# CODEOWNERS — Gemini Round-2 recommendation.
#
# Designates the enforcement-logic surfaces that should trigger explicit
# code-owner review if any change touches them. For this single-maintainer
# repo, CODEOWNERS is advisory: GitHub shows a "@timtrailor-hash review
# requested" badge on any PR touching these paths, forcing a deliberate
# pause before merge even when the author and owner are the same person.
#
# The simultaneous-modification attack (a PR that hollows portable-scenarios
# AND the integrity sentinels in one commit) fundamentally requires
# compromised commit access, at which point CI is theatre. This file raises
# the friction for an authorized maintainer making a mistake, not a
# defense against an attacker who already holds the admin key.

# Enforcement artifacts — any change here wants a conscious review pass.
.github/                       @timtrailor-hash
shared/git-hooks/              @timtrailor-hash
shared/hooks/                  @timtrailor-hash
verify.sh                      @timtrailor-hash
.conv_server_baseline          @timtrailor-hash
scenarios/drift/               @timtrailor-hash
scenarios/test_behavioral.py   @timtrailor-hash
scenarios/credentials/         @timtrailor-hash

# Host policy and service manifests — drift control surfaces.
hosts/                         @timtrailor-hash
machines/*/system_map.yaml     @timtrailor-hash
machines/*/services.yaml       @timtrailor-hash
machines/*/launchagents/       @timtrailor-hash
